<P>
   KOSOVO-TROOPS-ASSESS (Brussels) _ A military analysis: From the
military's point of view, planning for ground troops won't
accomplish much. What's needed to have a force ready by July or
August is putting the force together now: calling people up,
signing basing agreements, starting to move equipment. And if NATO
waits much longer it could miss goal of having force able to go in
before winter. By Michael R. Gordon.
