ago that a court officer released Eric Harris and Dylan Klebold
early from a juvenile diversion program, saying they had learned
the intended lessons in the months since their arrest and had
promising futures. ``Eric is a very bright young man who is likely
to succeed in life,'' the officer wrote in a report made public
here on Thursday. ``He is intelligent enough to achieve lofty goals
as long as he stays on task and remains motivated.'' By Jodi
Wilgoren and Dirk Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   COLO-SCHOOL-GUNS (Littleton) _ At a time when the gun industry
is battling lawsuits and other challenges, outrage over the high
school shooting is suddenly altering the debate over guns,
bolstering, at least for the time being, the political power of the
gun control advocates. By James Brooke.
