<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-CARDS-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MOORE TO SKIP MINICAMP 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE SCHOENFELD  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, ARIZ. - Unsigned wide receiver &UR; Rob Moore will not be at
Cardinals minicamp next week, his agent,  &UR; Gary Wichard, confirmed
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Wichard said the club didn't expect Moore to be there because he
is unsigned.
</P>
<P>
   Cardinals Vice President &UR; Bill Bidwill Jr. said he hadn't planned
on Moore attending.
</P>
<P>
   The team and Moore failed to reach agreement on a new contract
in February, and the team placed the franchise tag on him,
guaranteeing he would be paid the average of the top-five
receivers. The franchise tag also allows the Cardinals to match any
offer for him.
</P>
<P>
   Next season, the franchise figure for wide receivers is $3.531
million.
</P>
<P>
   Cardinals officials hope to sign Moore to longer than a one-year
deal. They likely will offer him a multiyear contract in July.
</P>
<P>
   If he signs a multiyear deal after July 15, the Cardinals will
get their franchise designation back for next season. &QL; 
Funds available &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The team has been given a rookie pool of $4.6 million to sign
its 11 draft picks, including two first-round choices, Ohio State
wide receiver &UR; David Boston and Eastern Michigan offensive tackl &UR; e
L.J.
 &UR; Shelton.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's going to be a little tight,'' said Bill Bidwill Jr., who
oversees contract negotiations.
</P>
<P>
   The $4.6 million rookie pool was the second to the expansion
Cleveland Browns' $5.1 million.
</P>
<P>
   New Orleans, which had only one draft pick, has $1.74 million to
spend on getting first-round pick  &UR; Ricky Williams, Texas running
back, signed. &QL; 
Public workout &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The team will hold an open practice on May 1 at Sun Devil
Stadium as part of its annual Select-A-Seat Block Party.
</P>
<P>
   The workout will be during the second day of the three-day
minicamp.
</P>
<P>
   Stadium gates open at 8 a.m. A children's autograph session is
scheduled for 10 a.m. to 10:30, followed by practice until noon. &QL; 
Short shots &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A four-day veterans camp is scheduled for May 10-13.
</P>
<P>
   Rookies and selected first- and second-year players will
participate in a two-week camp June 7-11 and June 14-18.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
