<HEADLINE>
COCKFIGHT RAID IS NO FEAST FOR VETERINARIAN 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By JOHN MacCORMACK  
 c.1999 San Antonio Express-News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN ANTONIO _ Dr. David Darter of the Crystal Veterinary Medical
Center is still waiting for the owners of about 20 fighting cocks
to show up and claim their birds, days after 270 roosters were
seized in a police raid of a huge cockfight.
</P>
<P>
   Nervous owners have been calling his Crystal City office since
the raid Sunday and asking about the confiscated gamecocks. Some
may go unclaimed, but Darter said he was not about to start heating
up the soup kettle.
</P>
<P>
   ``You can't eat these roosters,'' Darter said with a laugh.
</P>
<P>
   ``They're full of steroids and hormones. Some cockfighters even
used strychnine to keep them all fired up. Chicken soup is out of
the question,'' he said in a telephone interview.
</P>
<P>
   Rooster boarding rates at the clinic are $5 for the first day
and $3 for each subsequent day, and owners will have to pay the
charges to retrieve their birds. The unclaimed birds may soon be
put up for adoption.
</P>
<P>
   ``There may be a handful that the sheriff has to give away. Some
people are afraid to claim them for fear they'll be arrested, but
he's not even giving out tickets,'' said the only veterinarian in
Crystal City, a town of 8,200 people southwest of San Antonio.
</P>
<P>
   The raid happened Sunday morning when state troopers, sheriff's
deputies and constables descended upon a crowd of more than 300
people drawn by the blood sport.
</P>
<P>
   The event involved 400 to 500 birds. In addition to the 270
roosters seized, dozens more vanished into the brush in their
owner's hands and more than a 100 were found dead, victims of the
sport for which they are raised.
</P>
<P>
   ``Everyone was running every which way, and there were just
eight officers at the most,'' said Zavala County Sheriff Eusevio
Salinas.
</P>
<P>
   While dozens of people scrambled into the brush, Salinas said,
the authorities have more than four hours of videotape of cars and
faces of those who were there.
</P>
<P>
   He said charges may be filed against two men thought to have
organized the event.
</P>
<P>
   Cockfighting, although illegal in Texas, is still very popular,
as the guest list revealed.
</P>
<P>
   ``We had a county commissioner _ not from my county _ some other
local politicians from surrounding counties, and some school
teachers,'' the sheriff said.
</P>
<P>
   ``You know cockfighting is a culture, and those guys, the
cockfighters, are the real macho type, the tough hombres,'' Darter
said. ``They don't put up with any lip from their wives or anyone
else.''
</P>
<P>
   ``But when their roosters were impounded, they'd send their
mothers, their wives, their sisters and their daughters to get
them. Like they are afraid to come out and face the music. So the
macho image kind of dissolves,'' he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
