some slightly new territory in the movies-about-alpha-males
sweepstakes. By Jay Carr.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-KINKY (Undated) _ ``Hideous Kinky'' is neither hideous nor
kinky. It's a modest but unexpectedly affecting autobiography of a
daughter recalling her English hippie mother's spiritual quest in
Morocco and Algeria in 1972. By Jay Carr.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-LOST (Undated) _ Maybe David Spade can carry a movie
without the late Chris Farley, but you can't prove it by ``Lost &AMP;
Found.'' By Jay Carr.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-RELAX (Undated) _ ``Relax. . .It's Just Sex'' is a big,
bouncing puppy of a movie, an energetic crowd-pleaser so long as
the crowd includes the more liberal-minded among us. By Renee
Graham.
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC-CRANBERRIES (Undated) _ Irish band Cranberries has a new
CD called ``Bury the Hatchet,'' a new tour, and new energy. By
Steve Morse. 1140 worsd.
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC-ROCK (Undated) _ About ten years ago, Vic Chesnutt spent
an evening he can't recall that well, but one that turned out
fortuitous. By Jim Sullivan.
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-DREAM (Undated) _ Lendol Calder has taken on quite a
challenge: To find nice things to say about consumer credit. By
Charles Stein.
</P>
