saying there was no pre-nuptial agreement between her and the
champ. She was responding to Holyfield's divorce complaint, in
which he said she orally agreed that Holyfield could decide what
would be ``fair'' if they broke up. Fayette County Superior Court
Judge Ben Miller also signed a restraining order that prevents the
Holyfields from disposing of any assets. (Ellis, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 6-8.
