   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ATT-CABLE (Washington) _ Critics say AT&AMP;T's $62 billion offer to
buy the nation's fourth-largest cable TV operator will create a
colossus controlling cable rates, Internet access, and phone
service. Regulators are interested. By Aaron Zitner. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-IMF (Undated) _ As tensions over Yugoslavia increase with
the Russian government, the IMF meets to discuss extending $4.5
billion in aid for its battered &UR;  &LR; economy. By Kimberly Blanton. 700
words. (f and i coding)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   HKN-BRUINS (Greensboro, N.C.) _ During Game 1, Bruins center Tim
Taylor added a broken nose to his list of physical woes. By Nancy
Marrapese. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   HKN-BRUINS-THORNTON (Greensboro, N.C.) _ The ache, twinge, and
soreness around Joe Thornton's sternum, disappears. ``I'm 100
percent. . . . It will be good to be in the lineup.'' By Kevin Paul
Dupont.
</P>
