contemporary America, or at least the image of our society widely
held by young people.
</P>
<P>
   ``Why's it so tragic? It happens all the time,'' she shrugged.
To blame the high-school slaughter on an indifference to violence
would oversimplify an event with many roots. But I think it's one
cause, one that has infected American kids from coast to coast. By
STEVE WILSON. Story moved in the ``K'' category. &QL; 
