closed doors, the alliance's military commander, Gen. Wesley Clark,
offered a strikingly optimistic view of the war against Yugoslavia.
``We are winning,'' he declared. ``He is losing. And he knows it.''
The scorecard, however, is anything but that clear. By Steven Lee
Myers and Eric Schmitt.
</P>
