<HEADER>
A1115 &Cx1f; tad-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-COOKLIGHT-RECIPES24-C     04-23 0779
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COOKLIGHT-RECIPES24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    A taste of cooking light
 &HT;    By Reagan Walker
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Dozens of recipes will be demonstrated today and Sunday at
Cooking Light's Grandstand '99 festival at Turner Field. Visitors
will be able to purchase a booklet of many of the recipes for $2.
We offer one here just to whet your appetite.
</P>
<P>
   DESSERT
</P>
<P>
   Banana Split Pie
</P>
<P>
   12 servings
</P>
<P>
   Preparation time: 20 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Cooking time: 20 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Freezing time: 4 hours
</P>
<P>
   Atlantan Terri Evans will put this recipe, which she created, up
against nine other finalists' recipes in the Healthy Choice 5
O'Clock Challenge Recipe Contest today. The winner will be
announced Sunday and will receive $10,000.
</P>
<P>
   2cups Healthy Choice low-fat granola without raisins
</P>
<P>
   1tablespoon light-colored corn syrup
</P>
<P>
   1large egg
</P>
<P>
   Cooking spray
</P>
<P>
   1/4cup evaporated fat-free milk
</P>
<P>
   7miniature whipped, fluffy nougat-milk chocolate bars (such as 3
Musketeers miniatures)
</P>
<P>
   3cups Healthy Choice Vanilla Premium low-fat ice cream, softened
</P>
<P>
   3/4cup mashed ripe banana
</P>
<P>
   23.5-ounce cups of prepared Healthy Choice Double Chocolate
Fudge Pudding
</P>
<P>
   1tablespoon chocolate syrup
</P>
<P>
   12strawberries
</P>
<P>
   Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Place granola in a heavy-duty
zip-top plastic bag and coarsely crush granola using a meat mallet
or rolling pin. Combine crushed granola, corn syrup and egg in a
bowl and toss with a fork until moist. Press into bottom of a
10-inch deep-dish pie plate coated with cooking spray. Bake at 325
degrees for 20 minutes and cool completely on a wire rack.
</P>
<P>
   Combine milk and chocolate bars in a small mircrowave-safe bowl.
Microwave on high for 1 minute; stir until melted. Combine ice
cream, banana and chocolate bar mixture in a large bowl; spoon half
of mixture into prepared pie crust. Spread pudding evenly over ice
cream mixture. Spread remaining ice cream mixture evenly over
pudding. Drizzle chocolate syrup evenly over pie. Cover and freeze
4 hours until firm. Cut pie into small wedges; top each with a
strawberry.
</P>
<P>
   Per serving: 222 calories, 6 grams protein, 5 grams fat (percent
calories from fat, 20), 38 grams carbohydrates, 29 milligrams
cholesterol, 116 milligrams sodium, 2 grams fiber.
</P>
<P>
   Tuna Escabeche with
</P>
<P>
   Pineapple Wild Rice
</P>
<P>
   2 servings Prep time: 10 minutes Cooking time: 8 minutes
Chilling time: 2-3 hours
</P>
<P>
   It doesn't take fat to have flavor. Just try this sassy dish
created by Kevin Rathbun, chef of Atlanta's popular Nava
restaurant. If you can't find New Mexico red chili powder,
substitute with any other hot chili powder. The same goes for the
Thai chili paste _ other chili pastes available at your grocery
will work.
</P>
<P>
   1tablespoon granulated sugar
</P>
<P>
   3teaspoons course salt, divided
</P>
<P>
   1tablespoon New Mexico Red Chili Powder
</P>
<P>
   1teaspoon cumin powder
</P>
<P>
   1/2teaspoon dried thyme
</P>
<P>
   1teaspoon black pepper
</P>
<P>
   4tablespoon canola oil, divided
</P>
<P>
   2chunks of yellowfin tuna, 4-5 ounces each
</P>
<P>
   1tablespoon honey
</P>
<P>
   1/2cup champagne vinegar
</P>
<P>
   1/2cup white wine
</P>
<P>
   1tablespoon Thai chili paste
</P>
<P>
   2tablespoons shallots, minced, divided
</P>
<P>
   1/2teaspoon garlic, minced
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2teaspoons jalapeno, minced, divided
</P>
<P>
   4tablespoons cilantro, divided
</P>
<P>
   5whole slices of pineapple
</P>
<P>
   1cup wild rice, cooked
</P>
<P>
   1tablespoon lime juice
</P>
<P>
   In a stainless steel bowl, mix all the sugar, 2 teaspoons salt,
the chile powder, cumin powder, thyme, pepper and 2 tablespoons
canola oil. Completely coat the tuna with the rub. Place a medium
non-stick skillet over medium-high heat for about two minutes and
then add the tuna, searing on all sides, about 3 minutes. Remove
from heat. The tuna should be rare in the middle.
</P>
<P>
   Mix the honey, the champagne vinegar, the white wine, the Thai
Chile paste, 1 tablespoon of minced shallot, the garlic, 1/2
teaspoon of jalapeno and 1 tablespoon cilantro. Submerge the seared
tuna in the mixture and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
</P>
<P>
   In a non-stick skillet over medium heat, sear the pineapple
until browned, 4-5 minutes. Remove and dice. In a large bowl, mix
the cooked wild rice, 1 tablespoon shallots, 2 tablespoons canola
oil, the lime juice, 3 tablespoons cilantro leaves, 1 teaspoon
minced jalapeno and 1 teaspoon course salt. Chill until tuna is
ready.
</P>
<P>
   After 2-3 hours of chilling, remove tuna from brine juice and
thinly slice. Serve with the chilled rice mixture.
</P>
<P>
   Per serving: 530 calories, 33 grams protein, 18 grams fat
(percent calories from fat, 30), 61 grams carbohydrates, 51
milligrams cholesterol, 1,237 milligrams sodium, 4 grams fiber.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
