A1307 &Cx1f; tad-z
u r &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CAR-NASCAR-ADVANCE24-     04-23 0313
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CAR-NASCAR-ADVANCE24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Martin too slow for field in Busch
 &HT;    By Al Levine
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   TALLADEGA, Ala. _ Something's missing from today's Touchstone
Energy 300 Busch series race at Talladega Superspeedway: Mark
Martin failed to make a Busch event for the first time since 1993.
</P>
<P>
   Martin, the all-time winningest driver in the series with 36
victories, was too slow in the No. 60 Ford to make the Touchstone
field. His second-round qualifying effort Friday, 188.801 mph (or
50.720 seconds around the 2.66-mile track), was even slower than
his best lap of 188.913 mph in first-round qualifying Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   He wasn't among the 36 fastest cars and is ineligible for one of
the seven provisional spots since he's high in Winston Cup points
(third). Cup veteran Ken Schrader is on the pole.
</P>
<P>
   The last time Martin failed to qualify for a Busch race was in
1993 at Daytona but he drove Dale Jarrett's car in the race with
his own sponsorship. This year, Martin has six Busch starts with
two wins, three top-fives and is 12th in points.
</P>
<P>
   ``We ran three-tenths faster in practice this morning than we
qualified,'' Martin said. ``I felt pretty confident we would be OK
to make the race. Just before our run, the sun came out and it got
really humid. I was surprised we slowed down so much from what we
ran earlier.''
</P>
<P>
   Martin's disappointment had to be filtered by his disdain for
Talladega. He is uncomfortable with the speeds generated by
superspeedways but was scheduled to race three times on the track
this weekend: in the Busch race, the International Race of
Champions today and Sunday's Winston Cup DieHard 500.
</P>
<P>
   With Martin out of the race, there's only one Ford in it. But
only three had tried to qualify. There are 38 Chevrolets in the
field.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
