<SLUG> BC-BKN-MAVS-NOWITZKI-TEX </SLUG>
 
Nowitzki living up to advance billing 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DWAIN PRICE 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
SACRAMENTO, Calif. _ The first 10 weeks of Dirk Nowitzki's
introduction to American basketball were agonizing.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Nowitzki couldn't beat Tiny Tim off the dribble, couldn't defend
little Johnny next door and couldn't rebound with the Munchkins of
``Wizard of Oz'' fame.
</P>
<P>
   But two weeks ago, Nowitzki started attacking the basket and
muscling inside for rebounds, and his outside shot finally found
its intended target.
</P>
<P>
   Although Nowitzki's defense remains suspect, at least he's
approaching gamesaggressively, which is why Mavericks coach Don
Nelson decided to give him more minutes. Nowitzki likes to refer to
the past two weeks as a rebirth.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's been a good two weeks for me,'' Nowitzki said.
``\RNelson\S gave me a second chance, and it's worked our pretty
good, and I try to play aggressive every night.
</P>
<P>
   ``They told me they want my points, and I should play aggressive
on the offensive end. It's a lot of ups and downs still, but I'm
just trying to bring some consistency to the court.''
</P>
<P>
   In his past seven games, Nowitzki averaged 15 points and 6.3
rebounds and shot 48.7 percent. In his past five games, he averaged
17.8 points and 5.6 rebounds and shot 54.2 percent..
</P>
<P>
   That includes a career-high 29 points April 16 against Phoenix
when Nowitzki converted 10 of 16 shots. And it includes a 22-point,
10-of-13 from the field effort in Wednesday's 109-95 victory in
Houston.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's been good for a lot of games,'' Nelson said. ``All we can
do is just keep talking to him and try to teach him.''
</P>
<P>
   Nelson admits he made a mistake by declaring Nowitzki a
rookie-of-the-year candidate before this season started.
</P>
<P>
   ``He gave me a chance at the beginning of the season, and it
didn't really work out,'' said Nowitzki, who started the Mavericks'
first nine games. ``I did so many things wrong, and he had to take
me out of the starting five, for sure.''
</P>
<P>
   Nowitzki said he didn't face physical players on a game-by-game
basis in Germany like he does in the NBA.
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't have to play physical ball in Germany, because I'd
score my points anyway,'' Nowitzki said. ``We had some big guys in
Germany, but they were not as strong as the centers and power
forwards over here.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's so physical over here everywhere _ even under the basket
or outside _ and everybody plays more aggressive. That's what I
know you've got to play with every night in order to make something
happen.''
</P>
<P>
   Nowitzki's teammates say they like his aggressive play and want
to see it every game.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's gotten some confidence, and I think guys are taking him
lightly and not understanding that he can do a lot of things,''
guard Erick Strickland said. ``They're not being aggressive on him,
and he's taking it right to them like he should be.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's being aggressive, and he looks real fluid now.''
</P>
<P>
   Nowitzki's early struggles haunt him. His game was like the
stock market _ up and down _ and Nelson didn't even bother playing
him in an April 1 home game against the Los Angeles Clippers.
</P>
<P>
   ``Through the whole season I was frustrated and disappointed,
and I didn't play really good when I was on the court,'' Nowitzki
said. ``The whole season was pretty tough for me.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm just so glad that coach gave me a second chance, and I
want to make the most of it.''
</P>
<P>
   Standing tall Mavericks rookie Dirk Nowitzki is averaging 7.5
points and 3.3 rebounds per game and shooting 40.2 percent. He
averaged 15 points and 6.3 rebounds and shot 48.7 percent in his
past seven games. A game-by-game breakdown of those seven, starting
with the most recent: Opp. FG M-A Pts. Reb. Min. San Antonio 3-8 8
5 40 Houston 10-13 22 3 41 Phoenix 3-11 13 9 39 Portland 6-11 17 3
40 Phoenix 10-16 29 8 44 Minnesota 2-5 4 3 17 San Antonio 4-14 12
13 32
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
